        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 1:45PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 145 PM CDT, the public reported a strong thunderstorm over
Goodrich, or 7 miles south of Livingston, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Public.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Livingston, Goodrich, Lake Livingston State Park, and West
Livingston.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
